2.2 “You”
Any individual or legal entity exercising rights under this license.

2.3 “Noncommercial”
Use that is not primarily intended for or directed toward commercial
advantage or monetary compensation.

Noncommercial use includes, for example:
- Personal projects
- Educational use
- Hobby or open-source projects that are distributed for free

Noncommercial use does NOT include, for example:
- Selling the Software or derivative works
- Including the Software in a paid product (e.g., a paid game)
- Monetizing a product that uses the Software (ads, in-app purchases,
subscriptions, donations tied to access or features)
- Offering paid services, hosting, or consulting tied to the Software or
derivative works
- Using the Software in any product, service, or offering that generates
revenue

If there is uncertainty, the use should be considered commercial.

2.4 “Attribution”
The exact credit text contained in the NOTICE file.

